%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mega%20Black%20Hole%20In%20Distant%20Galaxy%20Sends%202%20Jets%20Of%20Energy%3A%20What%20It%20Means%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETwo%20mighty%20beams%20of%20energy%20have%20been%20detected%20shooting%20in%20opposite%20directions%20from%20a%20supermassive%20black%20hole%20inside%20a%20distant%20galaxy%20-%20the%20largest%20such%20jets%20ever%20spotted%2C%20extending%20about%20140%20times%20the%20diameter%20of%20our%20vast%20Milky%20Way%20galaxy.%20The%20black%20hole%20resides%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20galaxy%20about%207.5%20billion%20light-years%20from%20Earth.%20A%20light-year%20is%20the%20distance%20light%20travels%20in%20a%20year%2C%205.9%20trillion%20miles%20(9.5%20trillion%20km).%20Because%20of%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20for%20light%20to%20travel%2C%20looking%20across%20great%20distances%20is%20peering%20back%20in%20time%2C%20with%20these%20observations%20dating%20to%20when%20the%20universe%20was%20less%20than%20half%20its%20current%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlack%20holes%20are%20extraordinarily%20dense%20objects%20with%20gravity%20so%20strong%20that%20not%20even%20light%20can%20escape.%20Most%20galaxies%2C%20including%20the%20Milky%20Way%2C%20have%20a%20large%20black%20hole%20at%20their%20core.%20Some%20of%20these%20shoot%20jets%20of%20high-energy%20particles%20and%20magnetic%20fields%20into%20space%20from%20their%20two%20poles%20as%20they%20devour%20material%20such%20as%20gas%2C%20dust%20and%20stars%20falling%20into%20them%20due%20to%20their%20immense%20gravitational%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20jet%20structures%20documented%20in%20the%20new%20study%20-%20using%20the%20LOFAR%20(Low-Frequency%20Array)%20radio%20telescope%2C%20a%20network%20of%20antennas%20centered%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20-%20extend%2023%20million%20light-years%20from%20end%20to%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20super-heated%20jets%2C%20caused%20by%20the%20violent%20events%20around%20the%20black%20hole%2C%20are%20comprised%20of%20subatomic%20particles%20called%20electrons%20and%20positrons%2C%20and%20magnetic%20fields%2C%20moving%20at%20nearly%20the%20speed%20of%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20have%20nicknamed%20these%20two%20jets%20Porphyrion%20(pronounced%20poor-FEER-ee-ahn)%2C%20named%20after%20a%20giant%20from%20ancient%20Greek%20mythology.%20Porphyrion%20is%20about%2030%25%20longer%20than%20the%20previous%20record-holder%20for%20such%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJet%20systems%20like%20Porphyrion%20appear%20to%20be%20among%20the%20most%20energetic%20spectacles%20that%20have%20occurred%20in%20the%20universe%20since%20the%20Big%20Bang%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Caltech%20astrophysicist%20Martijn%20Oei%2C%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20event%20that%20initiated%20the%20universe%20about%2013.8%20billion%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20general%20understanding%20is%20that%20jets%20are%20formed%20when%20magnetized%20material%20falls%20onto%20a%20rotating%20black%20hole%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20astrophysicist%20and%20study%20co-author%20Martin%20Hardcastle%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Hertfordshire%20in%20England.%20%26quot%3BThey%20need%20to%20be%20sustained%20by%20a%20continued%20infall%20of%20matter%20into%20the%20black%20hole%2C%20something%20of%20the%20order%20of%20one%20solar%20mass%20(the%20mass%20of%20the%20sun)%20a%20year%20of%20material.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20jets%2C%20not%20visible%20to%20the%20naked%20eye%2C%20start%20out%20small%20and%20grow%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20known%20for%20a%20while%20that%20black%20holes%20can%20generate%20these%20jets.%20But%20what%20is%20interesting%20is%20that%20to%20generate%20a%20large%20structure%20like%20this%2C%20the%20jets%20must%20stay%20on%20for%20a%20long%20time%20-%20about%20a%20billion%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Hardcastle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Porphyrion%20jets%20reach%20far%20beyond%20their%20home%20galaxy%2C%20with%20an%20energetic%20output%20equivalent%20to%20trillions%20of%20stars%20like%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20equivalent%20to%20the%20energy%20released%20during%20the%20most%20cataclysmic%20cosmic%20collisions%3A%20for%20example%2C%20those%20that%20occur%20when%20two%20galaxy%20clusters%2C%20each%20sometimes%20containing%20thousands%20of%20galaxies%2C%20merge%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Oei%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20it%20extends%20so%20far%20from%20its%20parent%20black%20hole%20means%20that%20it%20may%20be%20carrying%20energy%2C%20particles%20and%20magnetic%20fields%20into%20the%20voids%20in%20the%20cosmic%20web%2C%20the%20gaps%20between%20groups%20and%20filaments%20of%20galaxies%20which%20we%20know%20make%20up%20the%20large-scale%20structure%20of%20the%20universe.%20This%20may%20help%20us%20to%20understand%20the%20ubiquitous%20magnetic%20fields%20in%20the%20present-day%20universe%2C%26quot%3B%20Hardcastle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20jets%20could%20heat%20up%20gas%20in%20interstellar%20space%2C%20shutting%20down%20the%20formation%20of%20new%20stars%20that%20requires%20cold%20clouds%20of%20gas%2C%20and%20could%20damage%20habitable%20planets%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Milky%20Way's%20supermassive%20black%20hole%2C%20in%20its%20current%20quiescent%20state%2C%20does%20not%20have%20such%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20key%20finding%20is%20that%20jets%20from%20black%20holes%20can%2C%20if%20circumstances%20are%20right%2C%20become%20as%20large%20as%20the%20universe's%20major%20cosmic%20structures%20-%20galaxy%20clusters%2C%20cosmic%20filaments%2C%20cosmic%20voids%2C%26quot%3B%20Oei%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20means%20that%20individual%20black%20holes%20can%20have%20a%20sphere%20of%20influence%20that%20extends%20way%20beyond%20the%20galaxy%20in%20which%20they%20reside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726733820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fn1btevfo_black-hole_625x300_19_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmega-black-hole-in-distant-galaxy-sends-2-jets-of-energy-what-it-means-6600509%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20black%20hole%20resides%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20galaxy%20about%207.5%20billion%20light-years%20from%20Earth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%221st%20Test%20LIVE%3A%20Jaiswal%2C%20Rahul%20Depart%20In%20Quick%20Succession%2C%20India%20In%20Trouble%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20vs%20Bangladesh%20Live%20Updates%2C%201st%20Test%20Day%201%20Live%20Updates%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0Hasan%20Mahmud%20is%20on%20fire%20today%20and%20he%20is%20troubling%20India%20with%20his%20fiery%20face.%20He%20has%20now%20taken%20his%20fourth%20wicket%20and%20his%20latest%20prey%20is%20Rishabh%20Pant%2C%20who%20departed%20after%20scoring%2039%20runs.%20After%20his%20departure%2C%20wicketkeeper-batter%20KL%20Rahul%20has%20joined%20Yashasvi%20Jaiswal%20at%20the%20crease%20for%20India.%20Jaiswal%20is%20standing%20solid%20for%20India%20and%20has%20brought%20up%20his%20half-century.%20Both%20the%20batters%20now%20aim%20to%20stitch%20a%20solid%20partnership%20and%20keep%20four-down%20India%20in%20the%20game.%C2%A0On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Bangladesh%20bowlers%20are%20eyeing%20some%20quick%20wickets%2C%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20India's%20batting%20lineup%20in%20check.%20Bangladesh%20skipper%20Najmul%20Hossain%20Shanto%20won%20the%20toss%20and%20opted%20to%20bowl%20against%20India%20in%20the%20first%20Test%20of%20the%20two-match%20series%20on%20Thursday%20in%20Chennai.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcri