-rcna171594%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENBC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20The%20company%20told%20the%20outlet%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20a%20Hungary-based%20entity%20called%20BAC%20Consulting%20was%20authorized%20to%20use%20Gold%20Apollo's%20branding%20and%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bdesign%20and%20manufacturing%20of%20the%20prodcuts%20are%20entirely%20handled%20by%20BAC.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECristiana%20B%C3%A1rsony-Arcidiacono%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20of%20BAC%2C%20denied%20making%20the%20pagers%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20NBC%20News%20and%20said%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20the%20intermediate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGold%20Apollo%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20Business%20Insider%20was%20not%20able%20to%20reach%20BAC%20Consulting%20for%20comment.%20The%20company's%20website%20appeared%20to%20be%20down%20as%20of%20Wednesday%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenzen-Jones%20said%20that%20while%20supply%20chain%20attacks%20are%20often%20thought%20of%20in%20the%20context%20of%20cyberattacks%2C%20%26quot%3Bsabotaging%20enemy%20supply%20lines%20has%20a%20long%20history%20in%20warfare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20published%20a%20story%20about%20a%20US-run%20covert%20program%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fatwar.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F11%2F07%2Fdirty-tricks-of-government-forces-where-deception-and-deadliness-meet-inside-a-gun%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooby-trapping%20ammunition%3C%2Fa%3E%20intended%20to%20be%20used%20by%20the%20Taliban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20size%20of%20Tuesday's%20attack%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20the%20targeting%20of%20an%20object%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhezbollah-decided-months-ago-switch-from-cellphones-pagers-just-exploded-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epager%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20weapons%20is%20what%20makes%20this%20operation%2