06%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPlastics%20and%20other%20manufactured%20materials%20surround%20us%20and%20contact%20even%20the%20healthiest%20food%2C%20potentially%20causing%20chemicals%20to%20accumulate%20in%20our%20bodies%2C%20a%20new%20study%20suggests.%20%3Cp%3Eminiseries%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20new%20evidence%20that%20chemicals%20can%20migrate%20to%20human%20bodies%20via%20material%20like%20plastic%20containers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20what%20the%20health%20risks%20may%20be%2C%20but%20at%20least%20a%20few%20of%20the%20chemicals%20are%20known%20hazards.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20say%20it's%20concerning%20that%20thousands%20of%20these%20food%20contact%20chemicals%20are%20showing%20up%20in%20humans%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20research%20suggests%20you're%20being%20exposed%20to%20thousands%20of%20chemicals%2C%20including%20hazardous%20substances%2C%20that%20can%20leach%20into%20the%20human%20body%20through%20food-%20and%20beverage-related%20material%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrinking-from-plastic-bottles-can-increase-diabetes-risk-new-research-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplastic%20bottles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20takeout%20containers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20surprise%20that%20our%20environment%20is%20full%20of%20contaminants%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-penises-testicles-male-fertility-plastic-health-environment-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicroplastics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20can%20accumulate%20in%20our%20bodies%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20researchers%20in%20a%20recent%20study%20were%20taken%20aback%20by%20just%20how%20many%20chemicals%20in%20our%20everyday%20items%20can%20migrate%20into%20humans%2C%20and%20said%20it's%20%26quot%3Bconcerning%26quot%3B%20that%20we%20don't%20fully%20understand%20the%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%2C%20led%20by%20scientists%20from%20a%20Swiss%20nonprofit%20called%20the%20Food%20Packaging%20Forum%20Foundation%2C%20looked%20at%20data%20on%20more%20than%2014%2C000%20food%20contact%20chemicals%20%E2%80%94%20substances%20in%20containers%20or%20other%20materials%20that%20touch%20what%20we%20eat%20and%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20September%2017%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D98f40f9124eaa010f2a0a4c0fb4f3c1e59d87c00a6f65522c297e9b5c22824cf%26postID%3D66eae69769657a7deb42dbab%26postSlug%3Dthousands-of-chemicals-entering-human-bodies-from-food-packaging-study-2024-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41370-024-00718-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJournal%20of%20Exposure%20Science%20and%20Environmental%20Epidemiology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20explained%20that%2025%25%20of%20the%20chemicals%20they%20were%20studying%20%E2%80%94%20about%203%2C601%20substances%20%E2%80%94%20showed%20up%20inside%20the%20human%20body%2C%20in%20samples%20including%20skin%2C%20hair%2C%20blood%2C%20breast%20milk%2C%20and%20fat%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20suggests%20manufacturing%20chemicals%20are%20migrating%20into%20our%20bodies%20from%20items%20we%20use%20to%20store%2C%20package%2C%20or%20cook%20our%20food.%20It's%20not%20just%20plastic%20either%2C%20since%20even%20paper%20or%20cardboard%20can%20contain%20substances%20like%20ink%20that%20can%20be%20problematic%20when%20it%20comes%20into%20contact%20with%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227fa7f62-8a96-4c1c-a5a6-1d66b9506469%5C%22%3ETrying%20to%20understand%20the%20health%20risks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20digging%20for%20clues%20to%20understand%20the%20impact%20of%20these%20chemicals%20on%20long-term%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20chemicals%20are%20known%20to%20be%20dangerous%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-causes-cancer-food-products-that-increase-your-cancer-risk-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarcinogens%20(cancer-causing)%20substances%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-toxic-chemical-phthalates-in-food-makeup-toiletries-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoxins%3C%2Fa%3E%20linked%20to%20hormone%20and%20reproductive%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20category%20is%20called%20PFAs%20(per-%20and%20polyfluoroalkyl%20substances)%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchart-how-long-hazardous-forever-chemicals-pfas-stay-in-blood-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforever%20chemicals%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20linger%20and%20accumulate%20in%20our%20bodies%20and%20in%20the%20water%20and%20soil.%20PFAs%20exposure%20is%20linked%20to%20some%20cancers%2C%20liver%20damage%2C%20and%20more%2C%20as%20well%20as%20possible%20developmental%20defects%20in%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20hazardous%20chemicals%20the%20study%20found%20in%20food%20and%20our%20bodies%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fwhat-is-bpa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBPA%3C%2Fa%3E%20(a%20toxic%20ingredient%20in%20packaging%20linked%20to%20hormone%20problems)%20and%20heavy%20metals%20that%20can%20cause%20harm%20to%20our%20DNA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20a%20lot%20we%20don't%20know%20about%20many%20of%20the%20other%20chemicals%20found%20in%20human%20samples%2C%20including%20whether%20they%20might%20be%20harmful%20or%20what%2C%20if%20any%2C%20amount%20is%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20number%20of%20chemicals%20we're%20exposed%20to%20through%20food%20and%20drinks%20could%20also%20be%20much%20higher%20than%20the%203%2C601%20estimated%20in%20the%20study%2C%20according%20to%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225746f6cb-2471-495d-9d89-a8d0cff3dc10%5C%22%3EPutting%20limits%20on%20chemical%20exposure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20same%20team%20of%20researchers%20previously%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F28893723%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20found%20government%20regulations%20aren't%20doing%20much%20to%20prevent%20chemical%20exposure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20some%20existing%20rules%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepa-hazardous-forever-chemicals-drinking-water-limits-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elimits%20on%20PFAs%20in%20drinking%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20legislation%20is%20slow%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20latest%20science%2C%20and%20sometimes%20too%20vague%20to%20enforce.%20Plus%2C%20there's%20so%20much%20we%20don't%20know%20about%20potential%20risks%20of%20chemicals%20that%20haven't%20been%20studied%20as%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20study%20is%20one%20crucial%20step%20in%20understanding%20how%20chemicals%20in%20our%20environment%20(and%20in%20our%20food)%20could%20affect%20our%20health%20long-term%2C%20and%20how%20we%20might%20be%20able%20to%20reduce%20the%20risks%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20work%20highlights%20the%20fact%20that%20food%20contact%20materials%20are%20not%20fully%20safe%2C%20even%20though%20they%20may%20comply%20with%20regulations%2C%20because%20they%20transfer%20known%20hazardous%20chemicals%20into%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Jane%20Muncke%2C%20senior%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20environmental%20toxicology%20expert%2C%20and%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20Food%20Packaging%20Forum%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20would%20like%20this%20new%20evidence%20base%20to%20be%20used%20for%20improving%20the%20safety%20of%20food%20contact%20materials%20%E2%80%94%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20regulations%20but%20also%20in%20the%20development%20of%20safer%20alternatives%2C%26quot%3B%20Muncke%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthousands-of-chemicals-entering-human-bodies-from-food-packaging-study-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726693221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb2d43d17aa3c7b2b3e8c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthousands-of-chemicals-entering-human-bodies-from-food-packaging-study-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Food%20containers%20and%20cookware%20are%20leaching%20more%20potentially%20hazardous%20chemicals%20into%20our%20bodies%20than%20previously%20thought%2C%20new%20research%20suggests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthousands-of-chemicals-entering-human-bodies-from-food-packaging-study-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20goes%20big%20with%20first%20interest%20rate%20cut%20in%20four%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726692396000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F76fb%2Flive%2F01fb3a60-75ca-11ef-9fef-0d3ac4d91310.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcz04md0zdrno%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20cut%20its%20key%20lending%20rate%20by%200.5%20percentage%20points%20-%20a%20larger%20cut%20than%20expected.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A287%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcz04md0zdrno%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcz04md0zdrno.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcz04md0zdrno.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saban%20Films%20Snaps%20Up%20Danny%20A.%20Abeckaser