t%20from%20her%20teachers%20left%20her%20feeling%20excluded%2C%20and%20her%20love%20for%20these%20activities%20was%20left%20in%20the%20lurch%20%E2%80%94%20only%20because%20of%20how%20she%20looked.%20%E2%80%9CI%20protested%20but%20no%20one%20helped.%20The%20discrimination%20made%20me%20change%20schools%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManisha%E2%80%99s%20life%20took%20a%20turn%20when%20she%20joined%20a%20new%20school%20and%20found%20friends%20and%20teachers%20who%20helped%20her%20regain%20her%20confidence.%20Drawing%20became%20her%20refuge.%20Channelling%20her%20pain%20into%20her%20art%2C%20she%20brought%20life%20into%20portraits%20that%20soon%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20many.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20those%20traumatic%20times%2C%20art%20helped%20me%20heal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20illustrations%2C%20particularly%20of%20celebrities%2C%20soon%20caught%20attention%2C%20going%20viral%20across%20social%20media.%20She%20fondly%20remembers%20one%20of%20her%20proudest%20moments%3A%20The%20day%20she%20gifted%20a%20portrait%20to%20Bollywood%20actress%20Deepika%20Padukone%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F331304%2Fdevanshi-yadav-shaheed-ramashray-welfare-society-bareilly-acid-attack-sexual-abuse-survivor%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%20role%20in%20the%20film%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EChhapaak%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManisha%E2%80%99s%20journey%20didn%E2%80%99t%20end%20there.%20She%20expanded%20her%20creative%20space%20by%20posting%20makeover%20videos%20on%20Instagram%2C%20boldly%20challenging%20traditional%20beauty%20standards.%20While%20she%20faced%20mockery%20from%20many%2C%20her%20family%20stood%20as%20her%20rock%2C%20helping%20her%20rise%20above%20the%20negativity.%20Gradually%2C%20her%20art%20also%20became%20a%20source%20of%20income%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Manisha%20is%20not%20just%20an%20influencer%20but%2